        <page n="01" image="va.au.rv.1864.03.18.01">
            <pageNote>On this page are a reprinted list of deserters from the 52nd Regiment of
                Virginia Volunteers; advertisements; a poem; the text of a proclamation from
                President Davis calling for a day of prayer and fasting; the text of the inaugural
                address of Governor Allen in Louisiana; and a series of letters from before the war
                between Governor John Letcher and Reverend Lewis P. Clover, formerly of Lexington,
                Virginia, expressing Letcher's views of the impending war.</pageNote>
        </page>
