                <summary>Appointments to the Baltimore Annual Conference of Preachers for 1864
                    include J. C. Dice of Staunton, R. Smith of Mt. Sidney, and W. S. Baird,
                    Principal of the Wesleyan Female Institute and member of the Staunton Quarterly
                    Conference, all three in the Rockingham District, and J. M. Grandin, Chaplain,
                    C. S. A., and L. W. Haslip, C. S. A., both members of the Staunton Quarterly
                    Conference. The Conference will meet again at New Market on the second Thursday
                    in March 1865.</summary>
